Gwener is the Celtic (Breton/Erse/Gaelic/Manx/Welsh) form of Venus, goddess of love.
(Wonder what this is in Galliero/Galician?)

Another Goddess of Love that also gives her name to a day, similar to our own Friday (Frigadaeg from Frigga/Freya, modern German Freitag). 

See also the romantic languages where the day is named after Venus.